genresAdvancedInfo.name: greek guitar
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Greek guitar music is a genre that showcases the versatility of the guitar in Greek music. It is often played solo or in small ensembles and features intricate fingerpicking and melodic lines. The music draws from traditional Greek melodies and rhythms, as well as other influences such as flamenco and jazz. The guitar is a central instrument in Greek music and this genre highlights its importance and beauty.
